article.description: — Jordan Walker's 30 points led UAB over South Alabama 76-68 on Sunday.
article.headline: Walker's 30 lead UAB past South Alabama 76-68
article.linkText: Walker's 30 lead UAB past South Alabama 76-68
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- — Jordan Walker's 30 points led UAB over South Alabama 76-68 on Sunday. Walker added eight assists and three steals for the Blazers (7-1). KJ Buffen scored 15 points and added 10 rebounds. The Blazers picked up their sixth straight win. The Jaguars (3-6) were led by Greg Parham, who posted 30 points. Isaiah Moore added 19 points for South Alabama. In addition, Owen White finished with 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
